erala/2020/03/30/coronavirus-covid19-kerala-pinarayi-vijayan-daily-cases.html|title=COVID-19: 32 more test positive in Kerala, total number rises to 234|date=|work=Malayala Manorama|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> A 49-year-old man from [[Kakinada]] and a 72-year-old man from [[Rajahmundry]] tested positive in [[Andhra Pradesh]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/amp/ap-reports-two-more-coronavirus-cases-total-rises-to-23/1784669|title=AP reports two more coronavirus cases, total rises to 23|author=|date=30 March 2020|website=outlookindia|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> Seventeen more cases were reported in [[Tamil Nadu]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/covid-19-cases-spike-tamil-nadu-17-new-cases-reported-monday-121438|title=COVID-19 cases spike in Tamil Nadu, 17 new cases reported on Monday|date=|work=The News Minute|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> One more case was confirmed in [[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]].<ref>{{cite web |title=One more tests positive for Covid-19 in Andaman and Nicobar Islands, total cases rise to 10| url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/andaman-and-nicobar-islands-coronavirus-positive-1661335-2020-03-30|website=indiatoday|author=| date= 30 March 2020|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date= 30 March 2020}}</ref> [[Gujarat]] confirmed six more cases - five from [[Bhavnagar]] and one from [[Ahmedabad]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/gujarat-reports-69-coronavirus-cases-six-deaths/1784794|title=Gujarat reports 69 coronavirus cases, six deaths|date=|work=Outlook|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> Eight more cases were registered in [[Madhya Pradesh]] - seven from [[Indore]] and one from [[Ujjain]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/madhya-pradesh-gets-8-new-covid-19-cases-total-reaches-47/article31203330.ece|title=Madhya Pradesh gets 8 new Covid-19 cases; total reaches 47|date=|work=The Hindu - Business Line|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Punjab]] registered three more cases - one each from [[Mohali]], [[Ludhiana]] and [[Patiala]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://m.tribuneindia.com/news/ludhiana-woman-dies-of-coronavirus-punjab-toll-3-now-63172|title=Ludhiana woman dies of coronavirus; Punjab toll 3 now|date=|work=The Tribune|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Jammu and Kashmir (union territory)|Jammu and Kashmir]] reported eleven more cases - eight from [[Kashmir Division|Kashmir]] and three from [[Jammu Division|Jammu]] division.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/11-test-positive-for-covid-19-in-j-k-tally-climbs-to-4920200330225635/|title=11 test positive for COVID-19 in J-K, tally climbs to 49|date=|work=ANI|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> Five more cases were confirmed in [[Chandigarh]] - an [[Non-resident Indian and person of Indian origin|NRI]] couple who reside in [[Canada]] and three local transmissions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.tribuneindia.com/news/chandigarh-reports-five-more-coronavirus-cases-tally-now-13-63201|title=Chandigarh reports five more coronavirus cases; tally now 13|author=|first=|date=30 March 2020|website=The Tribune|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> Seven more people tested positive in [[Telangana]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/covid19-telangana-reports-second-death-total-cases-at-77/1785602|title=COVID-19; Telangana reports second death; total cases at 77|date=|work=Outlook|access-date=|url-status=live}}</ref> Twenty-five more people tested positive in [[Delhi]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/25-new-coronavirus-cases-in-delhi-today-97-have-tested-positive-so-far-2203215|title=With 25 Cases Today, Delhi Coronavirus Numbers R