u0435\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0442\u0430 \u0441 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0438\u0447\u043d\u0438 \u043b\u0435\u0433\u043b\u0430 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0435 \u043d\u0430\u0434 \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u044f \u0441\u044a\u044e\u0437 |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref> However, Chief Health Inspector Angel Kunchev stated on 5 March that there is a shortage of medical personnel.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://btvnovinite.bg/predavania/tazi-sutrin/zashto-se-stigna-do-remont-na-remonta-pri-rektorata-i-graf-ignatiev.html |title=\u0410\u043d\u0433\u0435\u043b \u041a\u0443\u043d\u0447\u0435\u0432: \u0410\u043a\u043e \u0441\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u044f\u0432\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441, \u0449\u0435 \u0438\u043c\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043c \u0441 \u043d\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0438 |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the announcement of positive SARS-CoV-2 test results, the Bulgarian government immediately banned the exports of protective equipment and placed orders for masks and protective suits to local manufacturers. In addition, 30,000 masks and 50,000 protective suits will be delivered by Turkey.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/08/4038200_forsmajornoto_proizvodstvo_na_zashtitni_oblekla_i/ |title=\u0424\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043c\u0430\u0436\u043e\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0442\u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0437\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0449\u0435 \u0435 \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u043f\u0435\u0447\u0430\u043b\u0431\u0430 |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> Some 111,000 suits and masks are required every month and the government plans to distribute them to health workers, social assistants, law enforcement personnel and border guards.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/obshtestvo/balgarski-firmi-zapochvat-proizvodstvo-na-zashtitni-oblekla-i-maski |title=\u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0444\u0438\u0440\u043c\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0447\u0432\u0430\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0437\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> [[Stolichna Municipality|Sofia Municipality]] has increased disinfections to four times daily at public institutions and in public transport.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/sofia/merki-sreshtu-koronavirusa-v-sofiya-zapochvat-dezinfektsii-4-pati-dnevno |title=\u041c\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0438 \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0443 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0432 \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0438\u044f. \u0417\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0447\u0432\u0430\u0442 \u0434\u0435\u0437\u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438 4 \u043f\u044a\u0442\u0438 \u0434\u043d\u0435\u0432\u043d\u043e |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> Personnel in all hospitals was reportedly being screened for the disease,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnes.bg/obshtestvo/2020/03/08/niama-novi-zarazeni-s-koronavirus-izsledvat-nad-140-kontaktni.441430 |title=\u041d\u044f\u043c\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0438\u0437\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u0432\u0430\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u0434 140 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043d\u0438 |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> but in April a nurse in [[Vidin]] reported that she was refused a test after caring for a positive patient, as the hospital in the city had no testing kits.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dnes.bg/stranata/2020/04/04/otkazali-test-za-virusa-na-medsestra-ot-vidin.444798 |title=\u041e\u0442\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442 \u0437\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430 \u043e\u0442 \u0412\u0438\u0434\u0438\u043d |website=Dnes.bg |access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nBy mid-March, large-scale imports of protective equipment from Vietnam, China and India had begun. Many volunteers were also signing up to join the handling of the crisis, including [[Nikola Vaptsarov Naval Academy]] cadets.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dariknews.bg/novini/bylgariia/85-hil.-oblekla-i-15-hil.-maski-pristigat-ot-turciia-varnenskite-kursanti-gotovi-za-dobrovolci-2217405 |title=85 \u0445\u0438\u043b. \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0438 15 \u0445\u0438\u043b. \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u0430\u0442 \u043e\u0442 \u0422\u0443\u0440\u0446\u0438\u044f, \u0432\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043a\u0443\u0440\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u0433\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u0434\u043e\u0431\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u043b\u0446\u0438 |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, the Minister of Health Kiril Ananiev decreed wearing masks in public mandatory, both outdoors and indoors, despite nationwide protective equipment shortages and soaring prices.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dw.com/bg/%D0%B2-%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B0-%D0%B7%D0%B0%D0%B3%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%B0-%D1%88%D0%B8%D1%8F%D1%82-%D0%BF%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%B4%D0%BF%D0%B0%D0%B7%D0%BD%D0%B8-%D0%BC%D0%B0%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8-%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D0%B0%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%B4-%D0%BF%D0%BE-%D0%BC%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%B5%D0%BB-%D0%BE%D1%82-%D1%81%D1%8A%D0%B2%D0%B5%D1%82%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%BE-%D0%B2%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%B5/a-52926981 |title=\u0412 \u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u0417\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0430 \u0448\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043f\u0430\u0437\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0430\u043a\u043e\u0440\u0434. \u041f\u043e \u043c\u043e\u0434\u0435\u043b \u043e\u0442 \u0441\u044a\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0441\u043a\u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435. |date=26 Mar 2020 |website=www.dw.com |language=bg-BG |url-status=live |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mediapool.bg/prokuraturata-zapochna-delo-za-spekula-zaradi-maski-ot-10-lv-news305261.html |title=\u041f\u0440\u043e\u043a\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0447\u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0435\u043b\u043e \u0437\u0430 \u0441\u043f\u0435\u043a\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043e\u0442 10 \u043b\u0432. |date=26 Mar 2020 |website=mediapool.bg |language=bg-BG |url-status=live |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mh.government.bg/bg/novini/aktualno/grazhdanite-koito-se-namirat-v-zakriti-ili-na-otkr/ |title=\u0413\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435, \u043a\u043e\u0438\u0442\u043e \u0441\u0435 \u043d\u0430\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430\u0442 \u0432 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0438 \u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430, \u0442\u0440\u044f\u0431\u0432\u0430 \u0434\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0441\u044f\u0442 \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0430 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0430 |date=30 March 2020 |publisher=Ministry of Health |language=bg-BG |url-status=live |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> The policy seemed to contradict Ananiev's earlier statement from 9 March that producing the needed gear \"will take months\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/09/4038339_shte_sa_nujni_meseci_za_da_se_izrabotiat_nujnite_maski/ |title=\u0429\u0435 \u0441\u0430 \u043d\u0443\u0436\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0446\u0438, \u0437\u0430 \u0434\u0430 \u0441\u0435 \u0438\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u044f\u0442 \u043d\u0435\u043e\u0431\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430, \u043e\u0431\u044f\u0432\u0438 \u0410\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435\u0432 |date=9 Mar 2020 |website=dnevnik.bg |language=bg-BG |url-status=live |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> Under article 209a of the Health Law, which was passed on 13 March and does not discriminate between offenses, failing to wear a mask in public would result in a fine of BGN 5,000 (EUR 2,555).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mediapool.bg/noseneto-na-maska-stava-zadalzhitelno-obnovena-news305456.html |title=\u041d\u043e\u0441\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0434\u044a\u043b\u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043d\u043e (\u043e\u0431\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0430) |date=30 Mar 2020 |website=mediapool.bg |language=Bulgarian |url-status=live |access-date=30 Mar 2020}}</ref> On 31 March Ananiev rescinded the decree, citing \"a lack of public consensus\" on the measure.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.segabg.com/hot/category-bulgaria/gledayte-na-zhivo-vutreshniyat-i-zdravniyat-ministur-razyasnyavat-merkite/ |title=\u0417\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0441\u0442\u044a\u0440 \u0434\u0430\u0434\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043d \u0437\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0434\u044a\u043b\u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 |date=31 Mar 2020 |website=segabg.com |language=Bulgarian |url-status=live |access-date=31 Mar 2020}}</ref>\n\nNearly BGN 14,000,000 (EUR 7,160,000) had been donated by 3 April, with 48% coming from private companies, 26% from public campaigns, 19% from individual donors and 7% from foundations.<ref name=\"DnevnikApr3\" />\n\n=== Testing ===\nAs of 24 March, there are 5 laboratories testing for COVID-19 in the country with a capacity of 300 tests per day. The total number of tests done by March 26 was 6,454, with 264 confirmed cases and a rate of infection around 4.1%.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.capital.bg/politika_i_ikonomika/covid/2020/03/24/4045342_medicinskiiat_suvet_predlaga_masov_skrining_za/ |title=\u041c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u0441\u044a\u0432\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043b\u0430\u0433\u0430 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432 \u0441\u043a\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |access-date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, the Ministry of Health announced that the country now has the capacity to process between 1,000 and 1,200 tests per day, at an estimated cost of BGN 930,000 (EUR 475,000) per month. Two additional methods of testing would be introduced at later stages of the pandemic - fluorescence immunochromatographic tests (up to 20,000 per day) and the so-called 'quick' tests (up to 40,000 per day). Major General Ventsislav Mutafchiyski called all three types \"equally important\", as the PCR ones provided reliable data, while the fluorescence tests could speed up the process before quick ones are applied to establish how many people have acquired immunity.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://nova.bg/news/view/2020/03/27/282927/%D1%82%D1%80%D0%B8-%D0%B2%D0%B8%D0%B4%D0%B0-%D1%82%D0%B5%D1%81%D1%82%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B5-%D1%89%D0%B5-%D1%81%D0%B5-%D0%BF%D0%BE%D0%BB%D0%B7%D0%B2%D0%B0%D1%82-%D0%B2-%D1%80%D0%B0%D0%B7%D0%BB%D0%B8%D1%87%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%82%D0%B5-%D0%B5%D1%82%D0%B0%D0%BF%D0%B8-%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D0%B5%D0%BF%D0%B8%D0%B4%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%B8%D1%8F%D1%82%D0%B0-%D0%BE%D1%82-covid-19-%D0%B2%D0%B8%D0%B4%D0%B5%D0%BE/ |title=\u0422\u0440\u0438 \u0432\u0438\u0434\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0435 \u0449\u0435 \u0441\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0437\u0432\u0430\u0442 \u0432 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0435\u0442\u0430\u043f\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0435\u043f\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0438\u044f\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0442 COVID-19 (\u0412\u0418\u0414\u0415\u041e) |date=27 March 2020 |access-date=2 April 2020 |publisher=nova.bg |language=bg-BG}}</ref> However, Mutafchiyski later added that rapid tests are considered \"unreliable\" and therefore mass screening would be \"meaningless\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.mediapool.bg/shtabat-slozhi-tochka-na-temata-s-barzite-testove-news305209.html |title=\u0429\u0430\u0431\u044a\u0442 \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0438 \u0442\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u043c\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0441 \u0431\u044a\u0440\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0435 |date=25 March 2020 |access-date=3 April 2020 |publisher=Mediapool |language=bg-BG}}</ref>\n\nConversely, Prof. Radka Argirova, chairman of the National Expert Board in Virology at the Bulgarian Doctors' Union, urged increased rapid testing in order to discover asymptomatic cases, avoiding the chance of a future second peak and terminating the epidemic progression.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.btv.bg/video/shows/lice-v-lice/videos/prof-radka-argirova-virusat-trjabva-da-se-likvidira-pri-asimptomnite.html |title=\u041f\u0440\u043e\u0444. \u0420\u0430\u0434\u043a\u0430 \u0410\u0440\u0433\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430: \u0412\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u0442\u0440\u044f\u0431\u0432\u0430 \u0434\u0430 \u0441\u0435 \u043b\u0438\u043a\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0438 \u0430\u0441\u0438\u043c\u043f\u0442\u043e\u043c\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 |date=25 March 2020 |access-date=3 April 2020 |publisher=bTV |language=bg-BG}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 April, the Ministry of Health announced a total of 15,599 tests had been performed to date in eight laboratories across the country.<ref name=\"16ktests\" />\n\n=== Medication ===\nAfter testing positive for COVID-19, business magnate [[Kiril Domuschiev]] announced that his company will procure [[chloroquine]] from foreign sources and donate it to the national coronavirus task force. Chloroquine, a [[quinine]] drug, has shown positive effects on COVID-19 patients in China and France. The Bulgarian government is looking into import opportunities from China and domestic production by local pharmaceutical companies.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/na-fokus/novite-lekarstva-za-covid-19-shte-pomogne-li-hlorihinat-i-shte-go-polzvame-li-u-nas |title=\u041c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043a\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0443 COVID-19: \u0429\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0433\u043d\u0435 \u043b\u0438 \u0445\u043b\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0445\u0438\u043d\u044a\u0442 \u0438 \u0449\u0435 \u0433\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u043b\u0438 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 |access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref> Exports of all quinine-based drugs were prohibited until further notice, and 35,000 doses of quinine-based [[Analgin]] for export have been diverted for domestic consumption. Another 250,000 doses of the drug can reportedly be produced on a short notice by local pharmaceutical companies.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://segabg.com/hot/category-bulgaria/kiril-ananiev-zabrani-iznosa-na-hininovi-lekarstva |title=\u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043e\u0432 \u0432\u044a\u0437\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0410\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435\u0432 \u0434\u0430 \u043e\u0441\u0438\u0433\u0443\u0440\u0438 \u0445\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0431\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0435 |access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref> On 3 April, the government negotiated the delivery of 171,429 packs of [[hydroxychloroquine sulfate]] and 30,000 packs of [[azithromycin]] from the [[China National Pharmaceutical Group]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/politika/kupuvame-ot-kitay-lekarstva-za-lechenie-na-covid-19-za-nad-1-mln-lv |title=\u041a\u0443\u043f\u0443\u0432\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u043e\u0442 \u041a\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0439 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u043b\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0434 1 \u043c\u043b\u043d. \u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430 |website=Dir.bg |access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Bulgaria]]n biotechnology company Micar21 has been developing a general coronavirus vaccine in the past four years, and announced that it will begin clinical trials of a SARS-CoV-2 vaccine based on this research in mid-2020.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://focus-news.net/news/2020/03/10/2755591/kostadin-petkov-sofiya-teh-park-rabotim-s-inovativni-firmi-koito-sa-razrabotili-molekula-za-lechenie-na-koronavirus.html |title=\u041a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043d \u041f\u0435\u0442\u043a\u043e\u0432, \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0438\u044f \u0422\u0435\u0445 \u041f\u0430\u0440\u043a: \u0420\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0438\u043c \u0441 \u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u0444\u0438\u0440\u043c\u0438, \u043a\u043e\u0438\u0442\u043e \u0441\u0430 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043c\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u043b\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |date=10 March 2020 |access-date=10 March 2020 |agency=Focus}}</ref> The company announced that with government support in funding and shorter clinical trial protocols, the drug could be synthesised in two months.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.168chasa.bg/Article/8297522?fbclid=IwAR1el8pNxVpsZsbzZjE-LrDGO3XfZYaD4VdREstWaeX5yEGkasKHZlg-lmo |title=\u0425\u0438\u043c\u0438\u043a\u044a\u0442 \u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f \u0424\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0435\u0432: \u0414\u043e 2 \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0446\u0430 \u043c\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043c \u0434\u0430 \u0438\u043c\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0443 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Criticism ===\nGeorgi Todorov, a Bulgarian doctor with experience in viral breakouts in [[Ghana]], criticised the handling of the COVID-19 threat. In particular, Todorov stated that Bulgaria's health administration is so rife with [[nepotism]] that it cannot come up with any coherent response; as a result, infectious disease specialists were not taken into account when formulating response policies, and no specific locations were designated for potential COVID-19 cases. Todorov further assumed that infected individuals may have not been identified because of improper application of testing procedures.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://e-vestnik.bg/31900/barkat-s-testovete-za-koronavirus-u-nas-zatova-ne-otkrivat/?fbclid=IwAR2_fhX6HCxpaKAQ0m9dXidrJu8E1pmJRyauCyXW0XPA3wKb1viuUqxOy6Q |title=\u0411\u044a\u0440\u043a\u0430\u0442 \u0441 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0435 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441, \u0437\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u0435 \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0442 |date=4 March 2020 |access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Prof. Milan Milanov, former manager of Pirogov Hospital, the government's response was \"catastrophically delayed\", although he added that there's no room for panic as COVID-19 treatment was \"the same as with influenza\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.24chasa.bg/novini/article/8286282 |title=\u041f\u0440\u043e\u0444. \u041c\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043d \u041c\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432: \u041e\u0447\u0430\u043a\u0432\u0430\u043c \u0432\u0437\u0440\u0438\u0432 \u043e\u0442 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432 \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0438\u044f |access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Impact ==\n\nBulgaria recorded 31,643 newly registered unemployed for the period between 13 March to 1 April. From these, 17,793 claimants stated that job losses were a direct consequence of the pandemic, and 12,661 registered in the week 23\u201327 March alone, compared to 4,561 for the same period in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.segabg.com/hot/category-bulgaria/nad-31-000-bulgari-sa-ostanali-bez-rabota-13-mart-nasam |title=\u041d\u0430\u0434 31 000 \u0431\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438 \u0441\u0430 \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0442 13 \u043c\u0430\u0440\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0430\u043c |date=1 April 2020 |website=segabg.com |language=bg |access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref> A survey conducted by the Bulgarian Industrial Association showed only 8% of the companies were willing to use the government stimulus package, which quickly became colloquially known as 'the 60:40 measure'.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/biznes/2020/04/02/4049567_ot_shemata_6040_biha_se_vuzpolzvali_edva_8_ot_firmite/ |title=\u041e\u0442 \u0441\u0445\u0435\u043c\u0430\u0442\u0430 60/40 \u0431\u0438\u0445\u0430 \u0441\u0435 \u0432\u044a\u0437\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0435\u0434\u0432\u0430 8% \u043e\u0442 \u0444\u0438\u0440\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0435, \u0442\u0432\u044a\u0440\u0434\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0443\u0447\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0435 |date=2 April 2020 |website=dnevnik.bg |language=bg |access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref> The proposal envisions the government paying 60% of the impacted businesses' employee wages for up to three months, as long as the companies refrain from lay-offs.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/biznes/2020/03/30/4048117_priemaneto_na_dokumenti_za_durjavnite_pomoshti_za/ |title=\u041f\u0440\u0438\u0435\u043c\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0434\u043e\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u0434\u044a\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0449\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u0444\u0438\u0440\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0447\u0432\u0430 \u0443\u0442\u0440\u0435, \u043e\u0431\u0435\u0449\u0430 \u0421\u0430\u0447\u0435\u0432\u0430 |date=30 March 2020 |language=bg |access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Bulgaria]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Bulgaria]]\n[[Category:2020 in Bulgaria|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Health in Bulgaria]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Bulgaria]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Details of ongoing pandemic in Bulgaria}}\n{{Current disaster|event=pandemic|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Bulgaria\n| map1            = COVID-19_Outbreak_cases_in_Bulgaria.png\n| legend1         = <center>Number of confirmed cases by province (as of 4 April)<ref name=\"ESRI\">{{Cite web |url=https://esribulgaria.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/6e2c968cf38540f29a4311295dce390f |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 COVID-19 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u0440\u0438\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u044f\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f |date=28 March 2020 |website=ESRI Bulgaria: COVID-19 Tracker |language=bg-BG |access-date=29 March 2020}}</ref></center> {{legend|#fefeea|0 confirmed}}{{legend|#F2A88D|1\u20139 confirmed}}{{legend|#E36654|10\u201349 confirmed}}{{legend|#E5354B|50\u201399 confirmed}}{{legend|#87353F|100+ confirmed}}\n| disease         = [[coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]]\n| first_case      = [[Pleven]], [[Gabrovo]]\n| arrival_date    = 8 March 2020\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], [[China]] (globally)<br />local source unknown\n| deaths          = 21\n| website         = [https://www.mh.government.bg/bg/informaciya-za-grazhdani/potvrdeni-sluchai-na-koronavirus-na-teritoriyata-na-r-blgariya/ Bulgarian Ministry of Health]\n| confirmed_cases = 541\n| recovery_cases  = 39\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have spread to [[Bulgaria]] when the country's first case was confirmed on 8 March 2020, a 27-year-old man from [[Pleven]] and a 75-year-old woman from [[Gabrovo]]. Neither of the two had traveled to areas with known Coronavirus cases. The man tested positive for the virus after being hospitalized for a respiratory infection, and authorities announced plans to test several people who were in contact with the two individuals.<ref name=\"rferl.org\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.rferl.org/a/bulgaria-confirms-coronavirus-cases-amid-flu-outbreak/30475539.html |title=Bulgaria, Moldova Report First Coronavirus Cases |date=8 March 2020 |publisher=[[Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]]}}</ref> Two other samples in Pleven and Gabrovo were positive on 8 March.<ref name=\"focus-news.net\">{{Cite news |url=http://focus-news.net/news/2020/03/08/2754995/prof-todor-kantardzhiev-ot-pleven-imame-dve-polozhitelni-probi-za-koronavirus-ot-gabrovo-sashto.html |title=\u041f\u0440\u043e\u0444. \u0422\u043e\u0434\u043e\u0440 \u041a\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0434\u0436\u0438\u0435\u0432: \u041e\u0442 \u041f\u043b\u0435\u0432\u0435\u043d \u0438\u043c\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u0434\u0432\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043d\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u043e\u0442 \u0413\u0430\u0431\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e \u0441\u044a\u0449\u043e |date=8 March 2020 |access-date=8 March 2020 |language=Bulgarian}}</ref> [[Index case|Patient zero]] remains unknown.<ref name=\"actualno.com\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.actualno.com/healthy/oficialno-ima-chetiri-potvyrdeni-sluchaja-na-koronavirus-v-bylgarija-news_1440246.html |title=\u041e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u043d\u043e: \u0418\u043c\u0430 \u0447\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0440\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u044a\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f |date=8 March 2020 |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAfter the number of patients in the country had reached 23, the Bulgarian Parliament voted unanimously to declare a state of emergency from 13 March until 13 April.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://news.bnt.bg/news/ns-prie-s-palno-edinodushie-obyavyavaneto-na-izvanredno-polozhenie-v-cyalata-strana-1043195news.html |title=\u041d\u0421 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0435 \u0441 \u043f\u044a\u043b\u043d\u043e \u0435\u0434\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0434\u0443\u0448\u0438\u0435 \u043e\u0431\u044f\u0432\u044f\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0438\u0437\u0432\u044a\u043d\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0432 \u0446\u044f\u043b\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430 - \u041f\u043e \u0441\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u0438 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 |website=news.bnt.bg |language=bg |access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> A 14-day preventive house quarantine was introduced for citizens who have been in contact with a COVID-19 patient or have returned from an overseas region with high number of cases. For patients tested positive for the virus a 21-day house quarantine was introduced. This time span is counted from the day a subsequent test comes out negative after they have been treated in a hospital or at home. After the WHO has established that COVID-19 is more resilient than the initial data was showing, the National Crisis-management Staff increased the recovery house quarantine by a week to 28 days.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://dariknews.bg/novini/bylgariia/28-dnevna-karantina-za-zarazeni-s-koronavirus-2219086 |title=28-\u0434\u043d\u0435\u0432\u043d\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 - \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f |website=dariknews.bg |language=bg |access-date=2020-04-01}}</ref> With the continuing increase of COVID-19 cases on a daily basis, on 1 April the Bulgarian government requested that Parliament extends the state of emergency by one month until 13 May.\n\nAs of 6 April 2020, there are 541 confirmed cases in 25 out of 28 Bulgarian provinces, with 21 recorded deaths and 39 recoveries. A total of 15,899 tests had been performed by 5 April.\n\n== Background ==\nA National Crisis-management Staff was formed by the Bulgarian government on 5 March to deal with the coronavirus pandemic.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://nova.bg/news/view/2020/02/24/279057/%D1%81%D0%BF%D0%B5%D1%88%D0%BD%D0%B8-%D0%BC%D0%B5%D1%80%D0%BA%D0%B8-%D1%81%D1%80%D0%B5%D1%89%D1%83-%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%BD%D0%B0%D0%B2%D0%B8%D1%80%D1%83%D1%81%D0%B0-%D0%B8-%D1%83-%D0%BD%D0%B0%D1%81-%D0%BE%D0%B1%D0%B7%D0%BE%D1%80/ |title=\u0421\u043f\u0435\u0448\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0438 \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0443 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0438 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 (\u041e\u0411\u0417\u041e\u0420) |access-date=9 March 2020}}</ref> The Government has appointed [[Major general|Major General]] [[Professor]] Doctor [[Ventsislav Mutafchiyski]] as the Chairman of the Staff. MG Prof. Dr. Mutafchiyski is the Director of the [[Military Medical Academy (Bulgaria)|Military Medical Academy]] and the most senior medical officer of the [[Bulgarian Armed Forces]]. The MMA combines the military medical services of the country in their entirety with several hospitals in the capital Sofia and around the country. At the same time it is one of the country's leading medical institutions and possesses large medical treatment capacity and know-how. The Staff fulfills a direct operational role in the management of the crisis and its decisions are implemented through executive orders of [[Prime Minister of Bulgaria|Bulgaria's Prime Minister]] and the country's Minister of Health.\n\nOn 23 March a separate Medical Council for dealing with the coronavirus pandemic was appointed by the Prime Minister. The Council is chaired by Professor Kosta Kostov, a leading pulmonary disease expert. The Council's mission is to provide the government with complementary analysis and action proposals and the general public with professional guidance and information. Unlike the National Crisis-management Staff, which is a formal national institution with executive power and tasks, the Council has mostly a knowledge-based advisory role.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://btvnovinite.bg/bulgaria/prof-kostov-medicinskijat-savet-shte-raboti.html |title=\u041c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u0441\u044a\u0432\u0435\u0442 \u0449\u0435 \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u0441\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u044f\u043d\u0435 \u0441 COVID-19}}</ref> On 5 April the Medical Council dispersed after \"achieving its purpose\", according to its Chairman.<ref>{{cite web |title=\"\u041c\u043e\u0437\u044a\u0447\u043d\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u0442\u0440\u044a\u0441\u0442\" \u043a\u044a\u043c \u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0442\u043e \u0432\u0435\u0447\u0435 \u0449\u0435 \u0441\u044a\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0443\u0432\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0435\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u043b\u043d\u0430 \u0433\u0440\u0443\u043f\u0430 |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/04/04/4050521_mozuchniiat_trust_kum_pravitelstvoto_veche_shte/?ref=home_layer2 |website=dnevnik.bg |accessdate=6 April 2020 |language=bg |date=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Timeline ==\n=== 8 March ===\nOn 8 March 2020 [[Bulgaria]] confirmed its first two cases, a 27-year-old man from [[Pleven]] and a 75-year-old woman from [[Gabrovo]]. Neither of the two reported having traveled to areas with known coronavirus cases. The man tested positive for the virus after being hospitalized for a respiratory infection, and authorities announced plans to test several people who were in contact with the two individuals.<ref name=\"rferl.org\"/> Two other samples in Pleven and Gabrovo were found positive on 8 March.<ref name=\"focus-news.net\"/> [[Index case|Patient zero]] remains unknown.<ref name=\"actualno.com\"/>\n\nOn the same day, the hospital in Gabrovo requested additional personnel from other hospitals in the country, as it only had three [[communicable disease]]s specialists. All of its [[internal medicine]] specialists have been quarantined after one of the four initial cases was confirmed to be a nurse at the hospital.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/obshtestvo/gabrovo-poiska-podkreplenie-ot-infektsionisti-zaradi-dvata-sluchaya-na-covid-19 |title=\u0413\u0430\u0431\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e \u043f\u043e\u0438\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043a\u0440\u0435\u043f\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043e\u0442 \u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u043e\u043d\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u0434\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u044f \u043d\u0430 Covid-19 |date=8 March 2020 |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> The government issued a nationwide ban on closed-door public events.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/politika/pravitelstvoto-zabrani-vsichki-masovi-proyavi-na-zakrito-v-stranata |title=\u041f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e\u0442\u043e \u0437\u0430\u0431\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438 \u0432\u0441\u0438\u0447\u043a\u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u044f\u0432\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0442\u043e \u0432 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> The origin of the outbreak remains unknown, and the [[Ministry of Interior (Bulgaria)|Ministry of Interior]] is tracking down all individuals who have been in contact with the patients.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.vma.bg/newsitem.html?action=news&newsid=829 |title=\u0427\u0435\u0442\u0438\u0440\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u044f \u043d\u0430 COVID-19 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> As of 8 March, 254 suspected cases were under quarantine across the country.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://focus-news.net/news/2020/03/08/2755023/ministar-denitsa-sacheva-254-sa-bolnichnite-listove-s-karantina-za-koronavirusa-v-tsyalata-strana.html |title=\u041c\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0441\u0442\u044a\u0440 \u0414\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0430 \u0421\u0430\u0447\u0435\u0432\u0430: 254 \u0441\u0430 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0438\u0447\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043b\u0438\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0435 \u0441 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0432 \u0446\u044f\u043b\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0430 |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 10 March ===\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Bulgaria medical cases chart}}\nTwo additional cases were confirmed in Sofia on 10 March 2020: a 74-year-old man and his 66-year-old wife. Both have arrived from [[Lom, Bulgaria|Lom]] two weeks prior to admission.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/obshtestvo/za-oshte-dva-sluchaya-na-noviya-virus-u-nas-v-sofiya-saobshti-boyko-borisov |title=\u0417\u0430 \u043e\u0449\u0435 \u0434\u0432\u0430 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u044f \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 - \u0432 \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0438\u044f, \u0441\u044a\u043e\u0431\u0449\u0438 \u0411\u043e\u0439\u043a\u043e \u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043e\u0432 |access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/obshtestvo/pirogov-e-izoliran-zaradi-dvamata-novi-zarazeni-borisov-svikva-saveta-za-sigurnost |title=\u0416\u0435\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0442 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u043e\u0442\u043e \u0441\u0435\u043c\u0435\u0439\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0432 \"\u041f\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0432\" \u0435 \u043d\u0435\u043a\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043d\u0430, \u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043e\u0432 \u0441\u0432\u0438\u043a\u0432\u0430 \u0421\u044a\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0441\u0438\u0433\u0443\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442 |access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> The woman died on the next day, becoming the first COVID-19 victim in the country.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/11/4039345_koronavirusut_vze_purva_jertva_v_bulgariia/ |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u0432\u0437\u0435 \u043f\u044a\u0440\u0432\u0430 \u0436\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f |access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 11 March ===\nA suspected case of a 33-year-old man was reported by the Saint George Hospital in [[Plovdiv]] on 11 March.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://focus-news.net/news/2020/03/11/2756041/33-godishen-mazh-ot-selo-kadievo-e-priet-v-infektsioznata-klinika-na-umbal-sv-georgi-v-plovdiv-sas-samnenie-za-koronavirus.html |title=33-\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0448\u0435\u043d \u043c\u044a\u0436 \u043e\u0442 \u0441\u0435\u043b\u043e \u041a\u0430\u0434\u0438\u0435\u0432\u043e \u0435 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0435\u0442 \u0432 \u0418\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u043e\u0437\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043a\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0423\u041c\u0411\u0410\u041b \"\u0421\u0432. \u0413\u0435\u043e\u0440\u0433\u0438\" \u0432 \u041f\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0434\u0438\u0432 \u0441\u044a\u0441 \u0441\u044a\u043c\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> The same day, a 40-year-old woman in [[Varna]] showed COVID-19 symptoms on [[CT scan]], although regional health authorities have not yet confirmed the case.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnes.bg/stranata/2020/03/11/40-godishna-pripadna-vyv-varna-predpolagat-koronavirus.441831 |title=40-\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0448\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043f\u0430\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u0432\u044a\u0432 \u0412\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0430, \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0433\u0430\u0442 - \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 12 March ===\nBy 12 March, the number of cases had increased to 23, most of them in Sofia. Many of these had been in contact with the elderly couple admitted to the [[Pirogov Hospital]] on 10 March.\n\n=== 13 March ===\nOn 13 March, after 16 reported cases in one day, Bulgaria declared a state of emergency for one month until 13 April. Schools, shopping centres, cinemas, restaurants, and other places of business were closed. All sports events were suspended. Only supermarkets, food markets, pharmacies, banks and gas stations remain open.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://nova.bg/news/view/2020/03/13/281109/\u0431\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f-\u0432-\u0438\u0437\u0432\u044a\u043d\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u043e-\u043f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435-\u0437\u0430-1-\u043c\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0446 |title=\u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0432 \u0438\u0437\u0432\u044a\u043d\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0437\u0430 1 \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0446 |date=13 March 2020 |access-date=13 March 2020 |agency=Focus}}</ref> Additionally, all arrivals from Italy, Spain, Iran, South Korea and China were placed under a mandatory 14-day quarantine.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bgonair.bg/a/2-bulgaria/188624-mvnr-balgariya-ne-e-vavela-ogranicheniya-na-darzhavnite-si-granitsi |title=\u041c\u0412\u043d\u0420: \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f \u043d\u0435 \u0435 \u0432\u044a\u0432\u0435\u043b\u0430 \u043e\u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f \u043d\u0430 \u0434\u044a\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u0438 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0446\u0438 |access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> There were 13 breaches of quarantine; patients involved were returned to treatment facilities and warned of repercussions, including fines and prison sentences.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dariknews.bg/novini/bylgariia/samo-za-den-13-dushi-sa-narushili-zadylzhitelnata-karantina-izdirvat-gi-video-2216674 |title=\u0421\u0430\u043c\u043e \u0437\u0430 \u0434\u0435\u043d: 13 \u0434\u0443\u0448\u0438 \u0441\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0448\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0434\u044a\u043b\u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430, \u0438\u0437\u0434\u0438\u0440\u0432\u0430\u0442 \u0433\u0438 |access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 14 March ===\nOn 14 March, a second death and a third case in Pleven were reported. The second victim of the virus was the 74-year old husband of the first victim.<ref>[https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/14/4040910_vtora_jertva_na_koronavirusa_i_10_novi_zarazeni/ www.dnevnik.bg]</ref><ref>[https://www.mh.government.bg/bg/novini/aktualno/pochina-74-godishniyat-pacient-na-pirogov-pri-kojt/ \u041f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430 74-\u0433\u043e\u0434\u0438\u0448\u043d\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u043f\u0430\u0446\u0438\u0435\u043d\u0442 \u043d\u0430 \"\u041f\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0432\", \u043f\u0440\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0439\u0442\u043e \u0431\u0435\u0448\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u044a\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d COVID-19] ''www.mh.government.bg'' accessed 14 March 2020</ref> Late in the evening on 31 March a Member of Parliament was tested positive for the virus. All MPs were urgently tested on the following day. If some of them are also tested positive, the Parliament will be adjourned. Options for the MPs to continue their legislative work (including voting) online from home under isolation are being explored.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mediapool.bg/parlamentat-umuva-kak-da-raboti-sled-parviya-deputat-s-covid-19-news305584.html |title=Parliament is looking into ways to continue working after the first case of an MP positive for Covid-19 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== 15 March ===\nThe number of confirmed cases in Bulgaria rose to 51 on 15 March. A total of 83 tests were done at the Military Medical Academy, of which six were positive, and 51 were processed at the National Reference Laboratory, of which two were positive. In Varna, one test out of 12 samples proved positive.\n\n=== 16 March ===\nThe Ministry of Health announced that citizens from a number of countries would be prohibited from entering Bulgaria starting 00:00 on 18 March. These are China, Iran, Bangladesh, India, the Maldives, Nepal, Sri Lanka, Spain, Italy, South Korea, France, Germany, the Netherlands, Switzerland and the United Kingdom. Additionally, sanitary control units will be established on some border crossings with Serbia, North Macedonia, Greece and Romania.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnes.bg/obshtestvo/2020/03/16/nova-zapoved-zabraniava-vlizane-u-nas-na-grajdani-na-15-strani.442422 |title=\u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434 \u0437\u0430\u0431\u0440\u0430\u043d\u044f\u0432\u0430 \u0432\u043b\u0438\u0437\u0430\u043d\u0435 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 \u043d\u0430 \u0433\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438 \u043d\u0430 15 \u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0438! |access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref> The number of total cases rose to 62, including two British citizens vacationing in [[Bansko]].\n\n=== 17 March ===\n81 cases were reported, several linked to an outbreak in Bansko. None of the patients were in critical condition.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/obshtestvo/81-sa-veche-zarazenite-s-koronavirus-v-balgariya |title=81 \u0441\u0430 \u0432\u0435\u0447\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 18 March ===\nThe total number of cases increased to 94 by 18 March, with new cases appearing in [[Smolyan]], [[Veliko Tarnovo]] and [[Pernik]] among recent arrivals from outside the country. The previous day, Bansko became the first town in the country to be put under quarantine.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/obshtestvo/11-novi-polozhitelni-probi-virusat-stigna-smolyan-i-veliko-tarnovo |title=11 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043d\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u0438, \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u043d\u0430 \u0421\u043c\u043e\u043b\u044f\u043d \u0438 \u0412\u0435\u043b\u0438\u043a\u043e \u0422\u044a\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/obshtestvo/mayka-i-sin-sa-zarazenite-s-koronavirus-ot-pernik |title=\u041c\u0430\u0439\u043a\u0430 \u0438 \u0441\u0438\u043d \u0441\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u043e\u0442 \u041f\u0435\u0440\u043d\u0438\u043a |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 19 March ===\nOn 19 March the cases rose to 105 and an 80-year-old woman, who recently had a stroke, died from COVID-19 on the same day, making her the third victim from the disease in Bulgaria. Elsewhere, a 78-year-old Bulgarian citizen died from COVID-19 while visiting family in [[Pittsburgh]], [[Pennsylvania|PA]]. The woman, a choir conductor in Sofia, was uninsured and refused to seek medical attention.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.post-gazette.com/local/region/2020/03/25/Woman-who-died-of-COVID-19-refused-to-go-to-hospital-worried-about-bills/stories/202003250139 |title=Woman who died of COVID-19 refused to go to hospital, worried about bills, her son says |date=26 March 2020 |website=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette |access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 20 March ===\nThe total number of cases increased to 127 and the first recovery occurred.\n\n=== 21 March ===\nThe number of cases increased to 142 by noon, and three patients had recovered. Two cities, [[Dobrich]] and [[Shumen]], confirmed their first cases, the latter related to the Bansko cluster. There are 84 male and 58 female patients, the youngest being 4 years old, and the oldest 81 years old. More than 5,000 tests had been carried out, and an additional 10,000 tests would be made available at short notice.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/21/4044105_koronavirusut_v_bulgariia_izvunrednoto_polojenie/ |title=\u0413\u0435\u043d. \u041c\u0443\u0442\u0430\u0444\u0447\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438: 142 \u0441\u0430 \u0432\u0435\u0447\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 (\u0412\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043e) |date=21 March 2020 |access-date=21 March 2020 |publisher=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f: \u0418\u0437\u0432\u044a\u043d\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0442\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0432\u0435\u0440\u043e\u044f\u0442\u043d\u043e \u0449\u0435 \u0441\u0435 \u0443\u0434\u044a\u043b\u0436\u0438, \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0433\u043d\u043e\u0437\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u041a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0447\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432}}</ref>\n\n=== 24 March ===\nThe cases increased to 218 and the first case in Stara Zagora province was confirmed. A man from the town of [[Kazanlak]] was admitted in the Infectious unit in the hospital in [[Stara Zagora]]. He is believed to be 60 years old and returned from France on the 14th of March.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bgonair.bg/a/2-bulgaria/189351-zarazenite-s-koronavirus-u-nas-veche-sa-218-parvi-sluchai-v-stara-zagora |title=\u0417\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 \u0432\u0435\u0447\u0435 \u0441\u0430 218, \u043f\u044a\u0440\u0432\u0438 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u0432 \u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u0417\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0430 |date=24 March 2020 |access-date=24 March 2020 |publisher=Bulgaria ON AIR}}</ref>\n\n=== 25 March ===\nThe number of cases increased to 242 by the end of the day, with the city of [[Sliven]] reporting its first confirmed case. 16 new cases with no relation between them were registered in Sofia, with some being medical staff from a local hospital. Two new cases were confirmed in [[Blagoevgrad]], two in Plovdiv and one in Pleven. Two of the patients who were in critical condition were stabilized but remain \"in stable but severe condition\". One recovered completely, bringing the number of total recoveries to 5.\n\n=== 26 March ===\nA total of 22 cases were reported, bringing the overall number to 264. The coronavirus were registered for the first time in [[Kardzhali]] and [[Haskovo]]. 15 of the newly confirmed cases were in Sofia, 2 in Smolyan, one in Pleven, one in Veliko Tarnovo and one in Varna. Two people were admitted to hospital in critical condition, while three new patients recovered, bringing the number of recovered to 8. Two soldiers were confirmed to have be infected - one was stationed in Kosovo and was immediately brought back to Sofia, and the other contracted the virus in Romania, where he was hospitalised. The national quarantine was extended by additional two weeks and is now expected to finish on April 12.\n\n=== 27 March ===\n29 new cases were registered, with the total number reaching 293. From these, 17 were in Sofia, 5 in Plovdiv, 3 in [[Burgas]], and one each in Varna, [[Kyustendil]], Sliven and [[Pazardzhik]]. At least 93 people remained hospitalized, with 53 in Sofia alone.\n\n=== 28 March ===\nThe total number of cases reached 331, an increase of 38 from the previous day. The new cases included 19 in Sofia, 5 in Blagoevgrad, 4 in Burgas, 3 in Varna, 2 each in Kardzhali, Plovdiv and Shumen, and 1 in Smolyan. Four new deaths were also reported, with two occurring in Blagoevgrad and one each in Kyustendil and Sofia.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/28/4047390_koronavirusut_v_bulgariia_zarazenite_narasnaha_do_331/ |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f: \u0417\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043d\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0441\u043d\u0430\u0445\u0430 \u0434\u043e 331 (\u0445\u0440\u043e\u043d\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u044f) |date=28 March 2020 |access-date=29 March 2020 |publisher=Dnevnik}}</ref> The cases in Blagoevgrad, a mother and her daughter, were initially refused admission to the local hospital despite visible symptoms and had to request testing at a private lab; by the time the results came out as positive, the patients' condition had deteriorated significantly. They were eventually admitted and sent to intensive care, but both died shortly after.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dnes.bg/stranata/2020/04/01/za-ujasa-covid-19-razkazva-rodnina-na-pochinalite-maika-i-dyshteria-u-nas.444378,2 |title=\u0417\u0430 \u0443\u0436\u0430\u0441\u0430 COVID-19: \u0420\u0430\u0437\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0432\u0430 \u0440\u043e\u0434\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043c\u0430\u0439\u043a\u0430 \u0438 \u0434\u044a\u0449\u0435\u0440\u044f \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 |website=Dnes.bg |access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== 29 March ===\nA total of 15 new cases were reported, with 8 in Sofia, 3 in Plovdiv, and one each in Kardzhali, Sliven, Smolyan and Varna. Three new recoveries were also announced, while the number of deaths rose to 8 after a 51-year-old woman died in the Blagoevgrad hospital, one day after her mother had succumbed to the virus. The Ministry of Health announced that 125 out of 324 active cases remain hospitalized, with 13 of those in serious condition. The total number of tests performed exceeded 7,000, with 276 done on 29 March alone.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/29/4047568_koronavirusut_v_bulgariia_zarazenite_stanaha_346/ |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f: \u0417\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0430\u0445\u0430 346 |date=29 March 2020 |access-date=29 March 2020 |publisher=Dnevnik}}</ref>\n\n=== 30 March ===\nThirteen new cases were reported, with seven in Sofia and one each in Blagoevgrad, Kardzhali, Montana, Pleven, Plovdiv and Sliven, for a total of 359 cases. 113 patients remained hospitalized, with 13 in serious condition. Around 56% of all those infected so far were male versus 44% female, with a median age of 45. The total number of recoveries rose to 17.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/30/4048177_zarazenite_v_bulgariia_sa_359_niama_sluchai_v_novi/ |title=\u0417\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0441\u0430 359, \u043d\u044f\u043c\u0430 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u0432 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0430\u0441\u0442\u0438 |date=30 March 2020 |access-date=29 March 2020 |publisher=dnevnik.bg |language=bg-BG}}</ref>\n\n=== 31 March ===\nThe total number of confirmed infections increased by 40 to 399, and the first two cases were reported from the province of [[Silistra Province|Silistra]]. 20 of the new cases were registered in Sofia, four each in Burgas and Kyustendil, three each in Plovdiv and Varna, two in Silistra, and one each in Kardzhali, Pernik, Shumen and Stara Zagora. The number of hospitalized patients increased to 146, with 14 in serious condition, while 20 medical workers were announced to have contracted the disease so far. No new deaths or recoveries were announced. From the total of 399 confirmed cases, just under 57% (227) were male, versus 43% (172) who were female.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.mh.government.bg/bg/novini/aktualno/399-sa-potvrdenite-sluchai-na-covid-19-u-nas/ |title=399 \u0441\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u044a\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 COVID-19 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 |date=31 March 2020 |access-date=31 March 2020 |publisher=Bulgarian Ministry of Health (mh.government.bg) |language=bg-BG}}</ref>\n\n=== 1 April ===\nThe province of [[Ruse Province|Ruse]] reported its first case as part of 23 new infections across the country, bringing the total to 422. In addition to Ruse, 10 new cases were reported in Sofia, two each in Blagoevgrad, Burgas, Dobrich and Plovdiv, and one each in Haskovo, Kardzhali, Sliven and Stara Zagora. Two deaths were registered - a 57-year-old man in Kyustendil and a 40-year-old man in Sofia.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/04/01/4048818_koronavirusut_v_bulgariia_izvunrednoto_polojenie_shte/ |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f: \u0418\u0437\u0432\u044a\u043d\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0442\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0449\u0435 \u0441\u0435 \u0443\u0434\u044a\u043b\u0436\u0438, \u0436\u0435\u0440\u0442\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u0430 10 (\u0445\u0440\u043e\u043d\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u044f) |date=1 April 2020 |access-date=1 April 2020 |publisher=dnevnik.bg |language=bg-BG}}</ref> [[Hassan Ademov]] from the [[Movement for Rights and Freedoms]] became the first Bulgarian [[member of parliament]] to contract the virus, forcing the announcement of a mass test on 2 April that would cover government staff and all 240 MPs.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/politika/2020/03/31/4048787_deputat_ot_dps_e_s_koronavirus/ |title=\u0414\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0442\u0430\u0442 \u043e\u0442 \u0414\u041f\u0421 \u0435 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |date=1 April 2020 |access-date=1 April 2020 |publisher=dnevnik.bg |language=bg-BG}}</ref>\n\n=== 2 April ===\nThe total number of infections increased by 35 to 457, with the first case being reported from the province of [[Vidin Province|Vidin]]. The new cases included 20 in Sofia, four in Smolyan, three in Varna, two in Dobrich, and one each in Blagoevgrad, Montana, Pazardzhik, Plovdiv, Veliko Tarnovo and Vidin. No new deaths were reported, while the number of recoveries reached 25. 179 patients were currently hospitalized, with 18 in intensive care.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/04/02/4049299_koronavirusut_v_bulgariia_zarazeni_sa_458_dushi/ |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f: \u0417\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441\u0430 458 \u0434\u0443\u0448\u0438, \u0431\u0435\u0437\u0432\u044a\u0437\u043c\u0435\u0437\u0434\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0449 \u0437\u0430 \u0431\u0438\u0437\u043d\u0435\u0441\u0430 (\u0445\u0440\u043e\u043d\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0433\u0438\u044f) |date=2 April 2020 |access-date=2 April 2020 |publisher=dnevnik.bg |language=bg-BG}}</ref> A further two MPs were among the new cases, both from the ruling [[GERB]] party, including their parliamentary group speaker Daniela Daritkova.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/politika/2020/04/02/4049397_daniela_daritkova_i_deputat_ot_gerb_sa_s_koronavirus/ |title=\u0414\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435\u043b\u0430 \u0414\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0442\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u0438 \u0434\u0435\u043f\u0443\u0442\u0430\u0442 \u043e\u0442 \u0413\u0415\u0420\u0411 \u0441\u0430 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |date=2 April 2020 |access-date=2 April 2020 |publisher=dnevnik.bg |language=bg-BG}}</ref>\n\n=== 3 April ===\nThe National Assembly approved the government's proposal to extend the state of emergency by one month until 13 May.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.segabg.com/hot/category-bulgaria/gerb-udulzhi-izvunrednoto-polozhenie-podkrepata-na-dps |title=\u0413\u0415\u0420\u0411 \u0443\u0434\u044a\u043b\u0436\u0438 \u0438\u0437\u0432\u044a\u043d\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u043e\u0442\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u0441 \u043f\u043e\u0434\u043a\u0440\u0435\u043f\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0414\u041f\u0421 |date=3 Apr 2020 |website=segabg.com |language=Bulgarian |url-status=live |access-date=3 Apr 2020}}</ref> The confirmed case count reached 487, after 28 new infections were registered - 18 in Sofia, two each in Plovdiv and Smolyan, and one each in Blagoevgrad, Burgas, Kardzhali, Kyustendil, Veliko Tarnovo and Vidin. Four deaths were also announced, with one occurring late on the previous evening in Stara Zagora.<ref name=\"DnevnikApr3\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/04/03/4049902_koronavirusut_v_bulgariia_pochinalite_narasnaha_do_14/ |title=\u041a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f: \u041f\u043e\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043d\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0441\u043d\u0430\u0445\u0430 \u0434\u043e 14 \u0434\u0443\u0448\u0438 |date=3 April 2020 |access-date=3 April 2020 |publisher=dnevnik.bg |language=bg-BG}}</ref> Male patients continued to account for just under 57% of all cases (versus 43% female), with a median age of 47.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.mh.government.bg/bg/novini/aktualno/485-sa-potvrdenite-sluchai-na-covid-19-u-nas/ |title=485 \u0441\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0442\u0432\u044a\u0440\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0441\u043b\u0443\u0447\u0430\u0438 \u043d\u0430 COVID-19 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 |date=3 April 2020 |access-date=3 April 2020 |publisher=Bulgarian Ministry of Health (mh.government.bg) |language=bg-BG}}</ref>\n\n=== 5 April ===\nThe Ministry of Health announced that the total number of COVID-19 tests had reached 15,899, with 8 laboratories performing the procedure across the country.<ref name=\"16ktests\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.mh.government.bg/bg/novini/aktualno/obsho-15-899-testa-za-covid-19-sa-napraveni-u-nas/ |title=\u041e\u0431\u0449\u043e 15 899 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0430 COVID-19 \u0441\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u043f\u0440\u0430\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 |date=5 April 2020 |publisher=Ministry of Health |language=bg-BG |url-status=live |access-date=5 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n=== Cases ===\n{{Side box |metadata=No\n | above = '''Cases of coronavirus in Bulgaria'''\n | abovestyle = text-align:center\n | text = {{Graph:Chart\n  | type = line\n  | linewidth = 1\n  | showSymbols = 1\n  | width = 500\n  | height = 200\n  | showValues = offset:4\n  | xAxisTitle = Date\n  | xAxisAngle = -40\n  | x =8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar, 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 