0 |agency=Reuters}}</ref> A massive increase in influenza B cases prompted suspensions of routine medical examinations, and a recommendation by the government for suspension of lectures at universities.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.news.com.au/world/breaking-news/bulgaria-declares-influenza-epidemic/news-story/1bdd0a34e88af57da3206a9878a72603 |title=Bulgaria declares influenza epidemic |date=6 March 2020 |access-date=10 March 2020}}</ref> According to the latest Ministry of Health data, there were 2063 [[intensive care]] and 740 infectious disease hospital beds in the country, with a total of 1605 [[ventilator]]s across the health system.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/obshtestvo/osigurenostta-s-bolnichni-legla-v-balgariya-e-nad-srednata-za-evropeyskiya-sayuz |title=\u041e\u0441\u0438\u0433\u0443\u0440\u0435\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0442\u0430 \u0441 \u0431\u043e\u043b\u043d\u0438\u0447\u043d\u0438 \u043b\u0435\u0433\u043b\u0430 \u0432 \u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u044f \u0435 \u043d\u0430\u0434 \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043d\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0415\u0432\u0440\u043e\u043f\u0435\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u044f \u0441\u044a\u044e\u0437 |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref> However, Chief Health Inspector Angel Kunchev stated on 5 March that there is a shortage of medical personnel.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://btvnovinite.bg/predavania/tazi-sutrin/zashto-se-stigna-do-remont-na-remonta-pri-rektorata-i-graf-ignatiev.html |title=\u0410\u043d\u0433\u0435\u043b \u041a\u0443\u043d\u0447\u0435\u0432: \u0410\u043a\u043e \u0441\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u044f\u0432\u0438 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441, \u0449\u0435 \u0438\u043c\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043c \u0441 \u043d\u0435\u0434\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0438 |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the announcement of positive SARS-CoV-2 test results, the Bulgarian government immediately banned the exports of protective equipment and placed orders for masks and protective suits to local manufacturers. In addition, 30,000 masks and 50,000 protective suits will be delivered by Turkey.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/08/4038200_forsmajornoto_proizvodstvo_na_zashtitni_oblekla_i/ |title=\u0424\u043e\u0440\u0441\u043c\u0430\u0436\u043e\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0442\u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0437\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0449\u0435 \u0435 \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u043f\u0435\u0447\u0430\u043b\u0431\u0430 |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> Some 111,000 suits and masks are required every month and the government plans to distribute them to health workers, social assistants, law enforcement personnel and border guards.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/obshtestvo/balgarski-firmi-zapochvat-proizvodstvo-na-zashtitni-oblekla-i-maski |title=\u0411\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0444\u0438\u0440\u043c\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0447\u0432\u0430\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0438\u0437\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> [[Stolichna Municipality|Sofia Municipality]] has increased disinfections to four times daily at public institutions and in public transport.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/sofia/merki-sreshtu-koronavirusa-v-sofiya-zapochvat-dezinfektsii-4-pati-dnevno |title=\u041c\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0438 \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0443 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0432 \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0438\u044f. \u0417\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0447\u0432\u0430\u0442 \u0434\u0435\u0437\u0438\u043d\u0444\u0435\u043a\u0446\u0438\u0438 4 \u043f\u044a\u0442\u0438 \u0434\u043d\u0435\u0432\u043d\u043e |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> Personnel in all hospitals was reportedly being screened for the disease,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.dnes.bg/obshtestvo/2020/03/08/niama-novi-zarazeni-s-koronavirus-izsledvat-nad-140-kontaktni.441430 |title=\u041d\u044f\u043c\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0437\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u0441 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441, \u0438\u0437\u0441\u043b\u0435\u0434\u0432\u0430\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u0434 140 \u043a\u043e\u043d\u0442\u0430\u043a\u0442\u043d\u0438 |access-date=8 March 2020}}</ref> but in April a nurse in [[Vidin]] reported that she was refused a test after caring for a positive patient, as the hospital in the city had no testing kits.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dnes.bg/stranata/2020/04/04/otkazali-test-za-virusa-na-medsestra-ot-vidin.444798 |title=\u041e\u0442\u043a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442 \u0437\u0430 \u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430 \u043e\u0442 \u0412\u0438\u0434\u0438\u043d |website=Dnes.bg |access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nBy mid-March, large-scale imports of protective equipment from Vietnam, China and India had begun. Many volunteers were also signing up to join the handling of the crisis, including [[Nikola Vaptsarov Naval Academy]] cadets.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dariknews.bg/novini/bylgariia/85-hil.-oblekla-i-15-hil.-maski-pristigat-ot-turciia-varnenskite-kursanti-gotovi-za-dobrovolci-2217405 |title=85 \u0445\u0438\u043b. \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430 \u0438 15 \u0445\u0438\u043b. \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0433\u0430\u0442 \u043e\u0442 \u0422\u0443\u0440\u0446\u0438\u044f, \u0432\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0435\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043a\u0443\u0440\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u0433\u043e\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u0434\u043e\u0431\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u043b\u0446\u0438 |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, the Minister of Health Kiril Ananiev decreed wearing masks in public mandatory, both outdoors and indoors, despite nationwide protective equipment shortages and soaring prices.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dw.com/bg/%D0%B2-%D1%81%D1%82%D0%B0%D1%80%D0%B0-%D0%B7%D0%B0%D0%B3%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%B0-%D1%88%D0%B8%D1%8F%D1%82-%D0%BF%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%B4%D0%BF%D0%B0%D0%B7%D0%BD%D0%B8-%D0%BC%D0%B0%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8-%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D0%B0%D0%BA%D0%BE%D1%80%D0%B4-%D0%BF%D0%BE-%D0%BC%D0%BE%D0%B4%D0%B5%D0%BB-%D0%BE%D1%82-%D1%81%D1%8A%D0%B2%D0%B5%D1%82%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%BE-%D0%B2%D1%80%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%B5/a-52926981 |title=\u0412 \u0421\u0442\u0430\u0440\u0430 \u0417\u0430\u0433\u043e\u0440\u0430 \u0448\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043f\u0430\u0437\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0430\u043a\u043e\u0440\u0434. \u041f\u043e \u043c\u043e\u0434\u0435\u043b \u043e\u0442 \u0441\u044a\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0441\u043a\u043e \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u0435. |date=26 Mar 2020 |website=www.dw.com |language=bg-BG |url-status=live |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mediapool.bg/prokuraturata-zapochna-delo-za-spekula-zaradi-maski-ot-10-lv-news305261.html |title=\u041f\u0440\u043e\u043a\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0447\u043d\u0430 \u0434\u0435\u043b\u043e \u0437\u0430 \u0441\u043f\u0435\u043a\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0440\u0430\u0434\u0438 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u043e\u0442 10 \u043b\u0432. |date=26 Mar 2020 |website=mediapool.bg |language=bg-BG |url-status=live |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mh.government.bg/bg/novini/aktualno/grazhdanite-koito-se-namirat-v-zakriti-ili-na-otkr/ |title=\u0413\u0440\u0430\u0436\u0434\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435, \u043a\u043e\u0438\u0442\u043e \u0441\u0435 \u043d\u0430\u043c\u0438\u0440\u0430\u0442 \u0432 \u0437\u0430\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0438 \u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u0449\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0430, \u0442\u0440\u044f\u0431\u0432\u0430 \u0434\u0430 \u043d\u043e\u0441\u044f\u0442 \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0430 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0430 |date=30 March 2020 |publisher=Ministry of Health |language=bg-BG |url-status=live |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> The policy seemed to contradict Ananiev's earlier statement from 9 March that producing the needed gear \"will take months\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/bulgaria/2020/03/09/4038339_shte_sa_nujni_meseci_za_da_se_izrabotiat_nujnite_maski/ |title=\u0429\u0435 \u0441\u0430 \u043d\u0443\u0436\u043d\u0438 \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0446\u0438, \u0437\u0430 \u0434\u0430 \u0441\u0435 \u0438\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u044f\u0442 \u043d\u0435\u043e\u0431\u0445\u043e\u0434\u0438\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0438 \u0437\u0430\u0449\u0438\u0442\u043d\u0438 \u043e\u0431\u043b\u0435\u043a\u043b\u0430, \u043e\u0431\u044f\u0432\u0438 \u0410\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435\u0432 |date=9 Mar 2020 |website=dnevnik.bg |language=bg-BG |url-status=live |access-date=30 March 2020}}</ref> Under article 209a of the Health Law, which was passed on 13 March and does not discriminate between offenses, failing to wear a mask in public would result in a fine of BGN 5,000 (EUR 2,555).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.mediapool.bg/noseneto-na-maska-stava-zadalzhitelno-obnovena-news305456.html |title=\u041d\u043e\u0441\u0435\u043d\u0435\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0430 \u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0434\u044a\u043b\u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043d\u043e (\u043e\u0431\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0435\u043d\u0430) |date=30 Mar 2020 |website=mediapool.bg |language=Bulgarian |url-status=live |access-date=30 Mar 2020}}</ref> On 31 March Ananiev rescinded the decree, citing \"a lack of public consensus\" on the measure.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.segabg.com/hot/category-bulgaria/gledayte-na-zhivo-vutreshniyat-i-zdravniyat-ministur-razyasnyavat-merkite/ |title=\u0417\u0434\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u043c\u0438\u043d\u0438\u0441\u0442\u044a\u0440 \u0434\u0430\u0434\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043d \u0437\u0430 \u0437\u0430\u0434\u044a\u043b\u0436\u0438\u0442\u0435\u043b\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043a\u0438 |date=31 Mar 2020 |website=segabg.com |language=Bulgarian |url-status=live |access-date=31 Mar 2020}}</ref>\n\nNearly BGN 14,000,000 (EUR 7,160,000) had been donated by 3 April, with 48% coming from private companies, 26% from public campaigns, 19% from individual donors and 7% from foundations.<ref name=\"DnevnikApr3\" />\n\n=== Testing ===\nAs of 24 March, there are 5 laboratories testing for COVID-19 in the country with a capacity of 300 tests per day. The total number of tests done by March 26 was 6,454, with 264 confirmed cases and a rate of infection around 4.1%.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.capital.bg/politika_i_ikonomika/covid/2020/03/24/4045342_medicinskiiat_suvet_predlaga_masov_skrining_za/ |title=\u041c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0446\u0438\u043d\u0441\u043a\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u0441\u044a\u0432\u0435\u0442 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u043b\u0430\u0433\u0430 \u043c\u0430\u0441\u043e\u0432 \u0441\u043a\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043d\u0433 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |access-date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March, the Ministry of Health announced that the country now has the capacity to process between 1,000 and 1,200 tests per day, at an estimated cost of BGN 930,000 (EUR 475,000) per month. Two additional methods of testing would be introduced at later stages of the pandemic - fluorescence immunochromatographic tests (up to 20,000 per day) and the so-called 'quick' tests (up to 40,000 per day). Major General Ventsislav Mutafchiyski called all three types \"equally important\", as the PCR ones provided reliable data, while the fluorescence tests could speed up the process before quick ones are applied to establish how many people have acquired immunity.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://nova.bg/news/view/2020/03/27/282927/%D1%82%D1%80%D0%B8-%D0%B2%D0%B8%D0%B4%D0%B0-%D1%82%D0%B5%D1%81%D1%82%D0%BE%D0%B2%D0%B5-%D1%89%D0%B5-%D1%81%D0%B5-%D0%BF%D0%BE%D0%BB%D0%B7%D0%B2%D0%B0%D1%82-%D0%B2-%D1%80%D0%B0%D0%B7%D0%BB%D0%B8%D1%87%D0%BD%D0%B8%D1%82%D0%B5-%D0%B5%D1%82%D0%B0%D0%BF%D0%B8-%D0%BD%D0%B0-%D0%B5%D0%BF%D0%B8%D0%B4%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%B8%D1%8F%D1%82%D0%B0-%D0%BE%D1%82-covid-19-%D0%B2%D0%B8%D0%B4%D0%B5%D0%BE/ |title=\u0422\u0440\u0438 \u0432\u0438\u0434\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0435 \u0449\u0435 \u0441\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0437\u0432\u0430\u0442 \u0432 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0435\u0442\u0430\u043f\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0435\u043f\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0438\u044f\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0442 COVID-19 (\u0412\u0418\u0414\u0415\u041e) |date=27 March 2020 |access-date=2 April 2020 |publisher=nova.bg |language=bg-BG}}</ref> However, Mutafchiyski later added that rapid tests are considered \"unreliable\" and therefore mass screening would be \"meaningless\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.mediapool.bg/shtabat-slozhi-tochka-na-temata-s-barzite-testove-news305209.html |title=\u0429\u0430\u0431\u044a\u0442 \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0438 \u0442\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430 \u043d\u0430 \u0442\u0435\u043c\u0430\u0442\u0430 \u0441 \u0431\u044a\u0440\u0437\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0435 |date=25 March 2020 |access-date=3 April 2020 |publisher=Mediapool |language=bg-BG}}</ref>\n\nConversely, Prof. Radka Argirova, chairman of the National Expert Board in Virology at the Bulgarian Doctors' Union, urged increased rapid testing in order to discover asymptomatic cases, avoiding the chance of a future second peak and terminating the epidemic progression.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.btv.bg/video/shows/lice-v-lice/videos/prof-radka-argirova-virusat-trjabva-da-se-likvidira-pri-asimptomnite.html |title=\u041f\u0440\u043e\u0444. \u0420\u0430\u0434\u043a\u0430 \u0410\u0440\u0433\u0438\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430: \u0412\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u044a\u0442 \u0442\u0440\u044f\u0431\u0432\u0430 \u0434\u0430 \u0441\u0435 \u043b\u0438\u043a\u0432\u0438\u0434\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0438 \u0430\u0441\u0438\u043c\u043f\u0442\u043e\u043c\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 |date=25 March 2020 |access-date=3 April 2020 |publisher=bTV |language=bg-BG}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 April, the Ministry of Health announced a total of 15,599 tests had been performed to date in eight laboratories across the country.<ref name=\"16ktests\" />\n\n=== Medication ===\nAfter testing positive for COVID-19, business magnate [[Kiril Domuschiev]] announced that his company will procure [[chloroquine]] from foreign sources and donate it to the national coronavirus task force. Chloroquine, a [[quinine]] drug, has shown positive effects on COVID-19 patients in China and France. The Bulgarian government is looking into import opportunities from China and domestic production by local pharmaceutical companies.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/na-fokus/novite-lekarstva-za-covid-19-shte-pomogne-li-hlorihinat-i-shte-go-polzvame-li-u-nas |title=\u041c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u043a\u0430\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0443 COVID-19: \u0429\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0433\u043d\u0435 \u043b\u0438 \u0445\u043b\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0445\u0438\u043d\u044a\u0442 \u0438 \u0449\u0435 \u0433\u043e \u043f\u043e\u043b\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u043b\u0438 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441 |access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref> Exports of all quinine-based drugs were prohibited until further notice, and 35,000 doses of quinine-based [[Analgin]] for export have been diverted for domestic consumption. Another 250,000 doses of the drug can reportedly be produced on a short notice by local pharmaceutical companies.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://segabg.com/hot/category-bulgaria/kiril-ananiev-zabrani-iznosa-na-hininovi-lekarstva |title=\u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043e\u0432 \u0432\u044a\u0437\u043b\u043e\u0436\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u0410\u043d\u0430\u043d\u0438\u0435\u0432 \u0434\u0430 \u043e\u0441\u0438\u0433\u0443\u0440\u0438 \u0445\u0438\u043d\u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u0431\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438\u0442\u0435 |access-date=21 March 2020}}</ref> On 3 April, the government negotiated the delivery of 171,429 packs of [[hydroxychloroquine sulfate]] and 30,000 packs of [[azithromycin]] from the [[China National Pharmaceutical Group]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://dnes.dir.bg/politika/kupuvame-ot-kitay-lekarstva-za-lechenie-na-covid-19-za-nad-1-mln-lv |title=\u041a\u0443\u043f\u0443\u0432\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u043e\u0442 \u041a\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0439 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u043b\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u043d\u0430\u0434 1 \u043c\u043b\u043d. \u043b\u0435\u0432\u0430 |website=Dir.bg |access-date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Bulgaria]]n biotechnology company Micar21 has been developing a general coronavirus vaccine in the past four years, and announced that it will begin clinical trials of a SARS-CoV-2 vaccine based on this research in mid-2020.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://focus-news.net/news/2020/03/10/2755591/kostadin-petkov-sofiya-teh-park-rabotim-s-inovativni-firmi-koito-sa-razrabotili-molekula-za-lechenie-na-koronavirus.html |title=\u041a\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0434\u0438\u043d \u041f\u0435\u0442\u043a\u043e\u0432, \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0438\u044f \u0422\u0435\u0445 \u041f\u0430\u0440\u043a: \u0420\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0438\u043c \u0441 \u0438\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0442\u0438\u0432\u043d\u0438 \u0444\u0438\u0440\u043c\u0438, \u043a\u043e\u0438\u0442\u043e \u0441\u0430 \u0440\u0430\u0437\u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0438\u043b\u0438 \u043c\u043e\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0443\u043b\u0430 \u0437\u0430 \u043b\u0435\u0447\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 |date=10 March 2020 |access-date=10 March 2020 |agency=Focus}}</ref> The company announced that with government support in funding and shorter clinical trial protocols, the drug could be synthesised in two months.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.168chasa.bg/Article/8297522?fbclid=IwAR1el8pNxVpsZsbzZjE-LrDGO3XfZYaD4VdREstWaeX5yEGkasKHZlg-lmo |title=\u0425\u0438\u043c\u0438\u043a\u044a\u0442 \u0424\u0438\u043b\u0438\u043f \u0424\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0435\u0432: \u0414\u043e 2 \u043c\u0435\u0441\u0435\u0446\u0430 \u043c\u043e\u0436\u0435\u043c \u0434\u0430 \u0438\u043c\u0430\u043c\u0435 \u043b\u0435\u043a\u0430\u0440\u0441\u0442\u0432\u043e \u0441\u0440\u0435\u0449\u0443 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0430 |access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Criticism ===\nGeorgi Todorov, a Bulgarian doctor with experience in viral breakouts in [[Ghana]], criticised the handling of the COVID-19 threat. In particular, Todorov stated that Bulgaria's health administration is so rife with [[nepotism]] that it cannot come up with any coherent response; as a result, infectious disease specialists were not taken into account when formulating response policies, and no specific locations were designated for potential COVID-19 cases. Todorov further assumed that infected individuals may have not been identified because of improper application of testing procedures.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://e-vestnik.bg/31900/barkat-s-testovete-za-koronavirus-u-nas-zatova-ne-otkrivat/?fbclid=IwAR2_fhX6HCxpaKAQ0m9dXidrJu8E1pmJRyauCyXW0XPA3wKb1viuUqxOy6Q |title=\u0411\u044a\u0440\u043a\u0430\u0442 \u0441 \u0442\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0442\u0435 \u0437\u0430 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0443 \u043d\u0430\u0441, \u0437\u0430\u0442\u043e\u0432\u0430 \u043d\u0435 \u043e\u0442\u043a\u0440\u0438\u0432\u0430\u0442 |date=4 March 2020 |access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Prof. Milan Milanov, former manager of Pirogov Hospital, the government's response was \"catastrophically delayed\", although he added that there's no room for panic as COVID-19 treatment was \"the same as with influenza\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.24chasa.bg/novini/article/8286282 |title=\u041f\u0440\u043e\u0444. \u041c\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043d \u041c\u0438\u043b\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432: \u041e\u0447\u0430\u043a\u0432\u0430\u043c \u0432\u0437\u0440\u0438\u0432 \u043e\u0442 \u043a\u043e\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u0432\u0438\u0440\u0443\u0441 \u0432 \u0421\u043e\u0444\u0438\u044f |access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Impact ==\n\nBulgaria recorded 31,643 newly registered unemployed for the period between 13 March to 1 April. From these, 17,793 claimants stated that job losses were a direct consequence of the pandemic, and 12,661 registered in the week 23\u201327 March alone, compared to 4,561 for the same period in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.segabg.com/hot/category-bulgaria/nad-31-000-bulgari-sa-ostanali-bez-rabota-13-mart-nasam |title=\u041d\u0430\u0434 31 000 \u0431\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0438 \u0441\u0430 \u043e\u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0431\u0435\u0437 \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0430 \u043e\u0442 13 \u043c\u0430\u0440\u0442 \u043d\u0430\u0441\u0430\u043c |date=1 April 2020 |website=segabg.com |language=bg |access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref> A survey conducted by the Bulgarian Industrial Association showed only 8% of the companies were willing to use the government stimulus package, which quickly became colloquially known as 'the 60:40 measure'.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/biznes/2020/04/02/4049567_ot_shemata_6040_biha_se_vuzpolzvali_edva_8_ot_firmite/ |title=\u041e\u0442 \u0441\u0445\u0435\u043c\u0430\u0442\u0430 60/40 \u0431\u0438\u0445\u0430 \u0441\u0435 \u0432\u044a\u0437\u043f\u043e\u043b\u0437\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0435\u0434\u0432\u0430 8% \u043e\u0442 \u0444\u0438\u0440\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0435, \u0442\u0432\u044a\u0440\u0434\u0438 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0443\u0447\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0435 |date=2 April 2020 |website=dnevnik.bg |language=bg |access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref> The proposal envisions the government paying 60% of the impacted businesses' employee wages for up to three months, as long as the companies refrain from lay-offs.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.dnevnik.bg/biznes/2020/03/30/4048117_priemaneto_na_dokumenti_za_durjavnite_pomoshti_za/ |title=\u041f\u0440\u0438\u0435\u043c\u0430\u043d\u0435\u0442\u043e \u043d\u0430 \u0434\u043e\u043a\u0443\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u0434\u044a\u0440\u0436\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043c\u043e\u0449\u0438 \u0437\u0430 \u0444\u0438\u0440\u043c\u0438\u0442\u0435 \u0437\u0430\u043f\u043e\u0447\u0432\u0430 \u0443\u0442\u0440\u0435, \u043e\u0431\u0435\u0449\u0430 \u0421\u0430\u0447\u0435\u0432\u0430 |date=30 March 2020 |language=bg |access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Bulgaria]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Bulgaria]]\n[[Category:2020 in Bulgaria|coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Health in Bulgaria]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Bulgaria]]\n", "name_user": "Oksvobomchatka", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBackground", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_Bulgaria"}
{"title_page": "Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9", "text_new": "{{Other uses|Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9\n| settlement_type                 = [[District-level town (Vietnam)|Town (Class-4)]]\n| official_name                   = Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 Town\n| other_name                      = \n| native_name                     = Th\u1ecb x\u00e3 Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9\n| nickname                        = \n| motto                           = \n| image_skyline                   = \u0110\u1ea1i T\u00f2ng L\u00e2m T\u1ef1.jpg\n| imagesize                       = \n| image_caption                   = \u0110\u1ea1i T\u00f2ng L\u00e2m Temple\n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = \n| seal_size                       = \n| image_shield                    = \n| shield_size                     = \n| image_blank_emblem              = \n| blank_emblem_size               = \n| image_map                       = \n| mapsize                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| image_map1                      = \n| mapsize1                        = \n| map_caption1                    = \n| pushpin_map                     = \n| pushpin_label_position          = \n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|Vietnam}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Regions of Vietnam|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Southeast (Vietnam)|South East]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[Provinces of Vietnam|Province]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[B\u00e0 R\u1ecba-V\u0169ng T\u00e0u Province|B\u00e0 R\u1ecba-V\u0169ng T\u00e0u]]\n| seat_type                       = Capital\n| seat                            = [[Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 (ward of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 town)|Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9]]\n| government_type                 = \n| leader_title                    = \n| leader_name                     = \n| leader_title1                   = <!-- for places with, say, both a mayor and a city manager -->\n| leader_name1                    = \n| established_title               = \n| established_date                = \n| area_magnitude                  = \n| unit_pref                       = Imperial<!--Enter: Imperial, if Imperial (metric) is desired-->\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = 333.84\n| area_land_km2                   = \n| area_water_km2                  = \n| area_total_sq_mi                = \n| area_land_sq_mi                 = \n| area_water_sq_mi                = \n| area_water_percent              = \n| area_urban_km2                  = 187.33\n| area_urban_sq_mi                = \n| area_metro_km2                  = \n| area_metro_sq_mi                = \n| population_as_of                = 2019\n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = 221,030\n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_density_sq_mi        = \n| population_metro                = \n| population_density_metro_km2    = \n| population_density_metro_sq_mi  = \n| population_urban                = 155,114\n| population_density_urban_km2    = auto\n| population_density_urban_mi2    = \n| timezone                        = Indochina Time\n| utc_offset                      = +7\n| latd                            = \n| latm                            = \n| lats                            = \n| latNS                           = \n| longd                           = \n| longm                           = \n| longs                           = \n| longEW                          = \n| elevation_footnotes             = <!--for references: use <ref> </ref> tags-->\n| elevation_m                     = \n| elevation_ft                    = \n| postal_code_type                = <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code                       = \n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n}}\n\n'''Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9''' is a [[district-level town (Vietnam)|district-level town]] of [[B\u00e0 R\u1ecba-V\u0169ng T\u00e0u Province]] in the [[Southeast (Vietnam)|Southeast region]] of Vietnam. {{As of|2018}} the town had a population of 175,872.<ref name=492/NQ-UBTVQH14>{{cite web |url=https://thuvienphapluat.vn/van-ban/Bo-may-hanh-chinh/Nghi-quyet-492-NQ-UBTVQH14-2018-thanh-lap-thi-xa-Phu-My-phuong-thuoc-thi-xa-Phu-My-Vung-Tau-380114.aspx |title=Ngh\u1ecb quy\u1ebft s\u1ed1 492/NQ-UBTVQH14 c\u1ee7a \u1ee6y ban Th\u01b0\u1eddng v\u1ee5 Qu\u1ed1c h\u1ed9i v\u1ec1 vi\u1ec7c th\u00e0nh l\u1eadp th\u1ecb x\u00e3 Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 v\u00e0 c\u00e1c ph\u01b0\u1eddng thu\u1ed9c th\u1ecb x\u00e3 Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9, t\u1ec9nh B\u00e0 R\u1ecba - V\u0169ng T\u00e0u}}</ref> The town covers an area of 333.84&nbsp;km\u00b2.\n\nPh\u00fa M\u1ef9 was formerly '''T\u00e2n Th\u00e0nh District''', a rural district of B\u00e0 R\u1ecba-V\u0169ng T\u00e0u Province, with its district capital lying at Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 township. In 2018, T\u00e2n Th\u00e0nh District was dissolved to form the new district-level town of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9.\n\nThe town seat lies at [[Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 (ward of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 town)|Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9]] ward (former Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 township). Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 is a highly industrialized town with several industrial parks. Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 is home to [[deep water port]]s replacing [[Saigon Port]] when the latter relocated here. [[Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 Power Plant Complex]] with a total capacity of 4,000 MW contributes nearly 35% of Vietnam's total electricity.\n\n==Port of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9==\nThe '''Port of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9''' (pronounced Foo-me) serves as the main deep water cargo port for [[Ho Chi Minh City]], as well as for the [[resort]] town of [[V\u0169ng T\u00e0u]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Phu My Port - port and navigational information |url=http://www.vpa.org.vn/phu-my-port/ |website=www.vpa.org.vn |publisher=Vietnam ports association |accessdate=3 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Guide to port entry |date=2 January 2018 |publisher=IHS Port Guides |location=London }}</ref> The Port of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 is located 65&nbsp;km from Ho Chi Minh City and 45&nbsp;km from V\u0169ng T\u00e0u city.<ref>{{cite web |title=Day tours from Phu My Port |url=https://www.itourvn.com/blog/day-tours-from-phu-my-port |website=www.itourvn.com |publisher=\"I tour Vietnam\" Blog |accessdate=3 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=About Phu My Port |url=http://www.bariaserece.com/ |website=www.bariaserece.com/ |accessdate=3 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Administrative divisions==\nThe town is divided administratively into 5 wards and 5 communes:\n\n* [[Ch\u00e2u Pha]]\n* [[H\u1eafc D\u1ecbch]]\n* [[M\u1ef9 Xu\u00e2n]]\n* [[Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 (ward of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 town)|Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9]]\n* [[Ph\u01b0\u1edbc H\u00f2a, B\u00e0 R\u1ecba-V\u0169ng T\u00e0u|Ph\u01b0\u1edbc Ho\u00e0]]\n* [[S\u00f4ng Xo\u00e0i]]\n* [[T\u00e2n H\u1ea3i, B\u00e0 R\u1ecba\u2013V\u0169ng T\u00e0u|T\u00e2n H\u1ea3i]]\n* [[T\u00e2n H\u00f2a, B\u00e0 R\u1ecba\u2013V\u0169ng T\u00e0u|T\u00e2n H\u00f2a]]\n* [[T\u00e2n Ph\u01b0\u1edbc, B\u00e0 R\u1ecba\u2013V\u0169ng T\u00e0u|T\u00e2n Ph\u01b0\u1edbc]]\n* [[T\u00f3c Ti\u00ean]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{commons cat|Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9}}\n{{Cities in Vietnam}}\n{{Districts of Southeast Vietnam}}\n{{coord|10|34|50|N|107|05|06|E|region:VN_type:adm2nd_source:kolossus-viwiki|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Phu My Town, Ba Ria-Vung Tau}}\n[[Category:Districts of B\u00e0 R\u1ecba-V\u0169ng T\u00e0u Province]]\n[[Category:County-level towns in Vietnam]]\n{{BaRiaVungTau-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Other uses|Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9\n| settlement_type                 = [[District-level town (Vietnam)|Town (Class-4)]]\n| official_name                   = Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 Town\n| other_name                      = \n| native_name                     = Th\u1ecb x\u00e3 Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9\n| nickname                        = \n| motto                           = \n| image_skyline                   = \u0110\u1ea1i T\u00f2ng L\u00e2m T\u1ef1.jpg\n| imagesize                       = \n| image_caption                   = \u0110\u1ea1i T\u00f2ng L\u00e2m Temple\n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = \n| seal_size                       = \n| image_shield                    = \n| shield_size                     = \n| image_blank_emblem              = \n| blank_emblem_size               = \n| image_map                       = \n| mapsize                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| image_map1                      = \n| mapsize1                        = \n| map_caption1                    = \n| pushpin_map                     = \n| pushpin_label_position          = \n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|Vietnam}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Regions of Vietnam|Region]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Southeast (Vietnam)|South East]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[Provinces of Vietnam|Province]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[B\u00e0 R\u1ecba-V\u0169ng T\u00e0u Province|B\u00e0 R\u1ecba-V\u0169ng T\u00e0u]]\n| seat_type                       = Capital\n| seat                            = [[Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 (ward of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 town)|Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9]]\n| government_type                 = \n| leader_title                    = \n| leader_name                     = \n| leader_title1                   = <!-- for places with, say, both a mayor and a city manager -->\n| leader_name1                    = \n| established_title               = \n| established_date                = \n| area_magnitude                  = \n| unit_pref                       = Imperial<!--Enter: Imperial, if Imperial (metric) is desired-->\n| area_footnotes                  = \n| area_total_km2                  = 333.84\n| area_land_km2                   = \n| area_water_km2                  = \n| area_total_sq_mi                = \n| area_land_sq_mi                 = \n| area_water_sq_mi                = \n| area_water_percent              = \n| area_urban_km2                  = 187.33\n| area_urban_sq_mi                = \n| area_metro_km2                  = \n| area_metro_sq_mi                = \n| population_as_of                = 2019\n| population_footnotes            = \n| population_note                 = \n| population_total                = 221,030\n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_density_sq_mi        = \n| population_metro                = \n| population_density_metro_km2    = \n| population_density_metro_sq_mi  = \n| population_urban                = 155,114\n| population_density_urban_km2    = auto\n| population_density_urban_mi2    = \n| timezone                        = UTC + 7\n| utc_offset                      = +7\n| latd                            = \n| latm                            = \n| lats                            = \n| latNS                           = \n| longd                           = \n| longm                           = \n| longs                           = \n| longEW                          = \n| elevation_footnotes             = <!--for references: use <ref> </ref> tags-->\n| elevation_m                     = \n| elevation_ft                    = \n| postal_code_type                = <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n| postal_code                     = \n| area_code                       = \n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n}}\n\n'''Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9''' is a [[district-level town (Vietnam)|district-level town]] of [[B\u00e0 R\u1ecba-V\u0169ng T\u00e0u Province]] in the [[Southeast (Vietnam)|Southeast region]] of Vietnam. {{As of|2018}} the town had a population of 175,872.<ref name=492/NQ-UBTVQH14>{{cite web |url=https://thuvienphapluat.vn/van-ban/Bo-may-hanh-chinh/Nghi-quyet-492-NQ-UBTVQH14-2018-thanh-lap-thi-xa-Phu-My-phuong-thuoc-thi-xa-Phu-My-Vung-Tau-380114.aspx |title=Ngh\u1ecb quy\u1ebft s\u1ed1 492/NQ-UBTVQH14 c\u1ee7a \u1ee6y ban Th\u01b0\u1eddng v\u1ee5 Qu\u1ed1c h\u1ed9i v\u1ec1 vi\u1ec7c th\u00e0nh l\u1eadp th\u1ecb x\u00e3 Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 v\u00e0 c\u00e1c ph\u01b0\u1eddng thu\u1ed9c th\u1ecb x\u00e3 Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9, t\u1ec9nh B\u00e0 R\u1ecba - V\u0169ng T\u00e0u}}</ref> The town covers an area of 333.84&nbsp;km\u00b2.\n\nPh\u00fa M\u1ef9 was formerly '''T\u00e2n Th\u00e0nh District''', a rural district of B\u00e0 R\u1ecba-V\u0169ng T\u00e0u Province, with its district capital lying at Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 township. In 2018, T\u00e2n Th\u00e0nh District was dissolved to form the new district-level town of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9.\n\nThe town seat lies at [[Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 (ward of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 town)|Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9]] ward (former Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 township). Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 is a highly industrialized town with several industrial parks. Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 is home to [[deep water port]]s replacing [[Saigon Port]] when the latter relocated here. [[Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 Power Plant Complex]] with a total capacity of 4,000 MW contributes nearly 35% of Vietnam's total electricity.\n\n==Port of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9==\nThe '''Port of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9''' (pronounced Foo-me) serves as the main deep water cargo port for [[Ho Chi Minh City]], as well as for the [[resort]] town of [[V\u0169ng T\u00e0u]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Phu My Port - port and navigational information |url=http://www.vpa.org.vn/phu-my-port/ |website=www.vpa.org.vn |publisher=Vietnam ports association |accessdate=3 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Guide to port entry |date=2 January 2018 |publisher=IHS Port Guides |location=London }}</ref> The Port of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 is located 65&nbsp;km from Ho Chi Minh City and 45&nbsp;km from V\u0169ng T\u00e0u city.<ref>{{cite web |title=Day tours from Phu My Port |url=https://www.itourvn.com/blog/day-tours-from-phu-my-port |website=www.itourvn.com |publisher=\"I tour Vietnam\" Blog |accessdate=3 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=About Phu My Port |url=http://www.bariaserece.com/ |website=www.bariaserece.com/ |accessdate=3 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Administrative divisions==\nThe town is divided administratively into 5 wards and 5 communes:\n\n* [[Ch\u00e2u Pha]]\n* [[H\u1eafc D\u1ecbch]]\n* [[M\u1ef9 Xu\u00e2n]]\n* [[Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 (ward of Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9 town)|Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9]]\n* [[Ph\u01b0\u1edbc H\u00f2a, B\u00e0 R\u1ecba-V\u0169ng T\u00e0u|Ph\u01b0\u1edbc Ho\u00e0]]\n* [[S\u00f4ng Xo\u00e0i]]\n* [[T\u00e2n H\u1ea3i, B\u00e0 R\u1ecba\u2013V\u0169ng T\u00e0u|T\u00e2n H\u1ea3i]]\n* [[T\u00e2n H\u00f2a, B\u00e0 R\u1ecba\u2013V\u0169ng T\u00e0u|T\u00e2n H\u00f2a]]\n* [[T\u00e2n Ph\u01b0\u1edbc, B\u00e0 R\u1ecba\u2013V\u0169ng T\u00e0u|T\u00e2n Ph\u01b0\u1edbc]]\n* [[T\u00f3c Ti\u00ean]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{commons cat|Ph\u00fa M\u1ef9}}\n{{Cities in Vietnam}}\n{{Districts of Southeast Vietnam}}\n{{coord|10|34|50|N|107|05|06|E|region:VN_type:adm2nd_source:kolossus-viwiki|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Phu My Town, Ba Ria-Vung Tau}}\n[[Category:Districts of B\u00e0 R\u1ecba-V\u0169ng T\u00e0u Province]]\n[[Category:County-level towns in Vietnam]]\n{{BaRiaVungTau-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Alpha Centauri 5932", "label": "safe", "comment": "timezone", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ph%C3%BA_M%E1%BB%B9"}
{"title_page": "American Express - Virtual Reality (advertisement)", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox television advert\n| name               = American Express - Virtual Reality\n| image              =\n| image_size         =\n| caption            =\n| client             = \n| product            = [[Credit card]]\n| agency             = [[Ogilvy (agency)#Ogilvy & Mather|Ogilvy & Mather]], New York\n| writer             = Jim Jenkins\n| director           = [[David Kellogg]]\n| production company = [[Propaganda Films]], Los Angeles\n| producer           = [[Brendan O'Malley]]\n| starring           = {{hlist |[[Raymond O'Connor]] |[[Angelica Bridges]] | [[Brian Klugman]]}}\n| music              = Craig Snyder\n| released           = 1998\n| slogan             = \"Do more\"\n| runtime            = 1:01\n| country            = [[United States]]\n| language           = [[English language|English]]\n| budget             =\n| preceded_by        =\n| followed_by        =\n| website            =\n}}\n\n'''\"American Express - Virtual Reality\"''' is the name<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121127201412/http://www.tvspots.tv/video/6484/AMERICAN-EXPRESS--VIRTUAL-REALITY|title=AMERICAN EXPRESS - VIRTUAL REALITY|last= |first= |date= |website=Tv spots and commercials|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> of a television advertisement for the [[American Express]] [[Multinational corporation|multinational]] [[financial services]] corporation, created in 1998.<ref>{{YouTube|title=KCYU-LP/Fox commercials, 2/5/1998 part 4|id=n9vv5lZa658}}</ref> Directed by [[David Kellogg]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.adforum.com/talent/13106-david-kellogg|title=David Kellogg|last= |first= |date= |website=AdForum Talent: The creative industry network.|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> the spot is one in a series of [[Visa Inc.|Visa]]-bashing ads.\n\n==Synopsis== \nA man ([[Raymond O'Connor]]) finds happiness in a [[romantic fantasy]] of himself [[Ballroom dance|ballroom dancing]] in the arms of a [[Red hair|red-haired]] beauty ([[Angelica Bridges]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203003808/http://www.angelicabridges.com/about.php|title=Angelica Bridges|last= |first= |date= |website=angelicabridges.com|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://vimeo.com/90712946|title=ANGELICA BRIDGES TV APPEARANCES, COMMERCIALS, MODELING CAMPAIGNS, MUSIC VIDEOS, PRESS COVERAGE|last=Bridges|first=Angelica|date= |website=Vimeo|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>). That is until a store clerk<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=August 27, 1998|title=And the Winner Is ...|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1998-aug-27-fi-16964-story.html|work=Los Angeles Times|location= |access-date= }}</ref> ([[Brian Klugman]]) yanks the [[virtual reality]] [[Virtual reality headset|device]] that produced her. The clerk tells the man that he put himself above his [[Visa Inc.|Visa]] [[Credit limit|credit card limit]]. Unlike Visa, [[American Express]] has no pre-set limits. A [[Tug of war|tug-of-war]] quickly ensues between the man and the clerk, which ultimately results in the [[police]] being called.\n\n==Reception==\nThe commercial was [[50th Primetime Emmy Awards|nominated]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/style/tv/features/emmynomlist98.htm|title=1998 Emmy Nominations|last= |first= |date=July 23, 1998|website=Washington Post|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last= Elliott|first=Stuart|date=July 28, 1998|title=THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA; TV Ads Nominated For Emmy Awards|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1998/07/28/business/the-media-business-advertising-addenda-tv-ads-nominated-for-emmy-awards.html|work=The New York Times|location= |access-date= }}</ref> for an [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Commercial|Emmy for Outstanding Commercial]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.emmys.com/shows/american-express-virtual-reality|title=American Express - Virtual Reality |last= |first= |date= |website=Television Academy|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1998-jul-24-fi-6630-story.html|title=L.A. Basks in Glow of Ads Up for Emmy|last=Gellene|first=Denise|date=July 24, 1998|website=Los Angeles Times|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> ultimately losing out to [[Apple, Inc.|Apple Computer]]'s \"[[Think different|Think Different]]\" advertisement.\n\nAngelica Bridges, who portrayed to the red-headed beauty was compared to a modern-day [[Ginger Rogers]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/0KGAB8zNCb/|title=American Express Commercial \ud83d\udc83 #ballroomdancing #virtualreality#Tbt #emmynominated #fredastaire #gingerrodgers #screenshots #superbowlad|last=Bridges|first=Angelica|date=March 12, 2015|website=Instagram|publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref> Meanwhile, according to the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', this particular ad helped\n[[Raymond O'Connor]], the hapless Visa user, land a role in the film ''[[My Giant]]''.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Virtual reality in fiction]]\n*[[Dance in film#Ballroom]]\n*[[American Express#Advertising campaigns]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{imdb title|id=11703472|title=American Express - Virtual Reality}}\n\n{{American Express}}\n{{Mixed reality}}\n\n[[Category:American Express|Virtual Reality]]\n[[Category:American television commercials]]\n[[Category:1998 works]]\n[[Category:1998 in American television]]\n[[Category:Virtual reality in fiction]]\n[[Category:Works about ballroom dance]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television advert\n| name               = American Express - Virtual Reality\n| image              =\n| image_size         =\n| caption            =\n| client             = \n| product            = [[Credit card]]\n| agency             = [[Ogilvy_(agency)#Ogilvy_&_Mather|Ogilvy & Mather]], New York\n| writer             = Jim Jenkins\n| directo